  "prompt": "How can watery and white discharge be treated?",
  "response": "Watery and white discharge can have various causes, and treatment depends on the underlying reason:\n\n1. Normal vaginal discharge\n- Usually doesn't require treatment\n- Maintain good hygiene\n- Wear breathable cotton underwear\n\n2. Yeast infection\n- Over-the-counter antifungal creams\n- Prescription oral or topical antifungal medication\n- Probiotics\n- Avoid tight clothing\n\n3. Bacterial vaginosis\n- Prescription antibiotics\n- Maintain proper vaginal pH\n- Avoid douching\n\n4. Hormonal changes\n- Birth control regulation\n- Hormone replacement therapy\n- Lifestyle adjustments\n\n5. Sexually transmitted infections\n- Consult a healthcare professional\n- Prescription antibiotics or antiviral medications\n- Partner treatment may be necessary\n\n6. General recommendations\n- Practice safe sex\n- Maintain good personal hygiene\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Avoid irritating products\n\n7. When to see a doctor\n- Discharge with unusual color or odor\n- Accompanied by pain or itching\n- Persistent symptoms\n- Fever or other concerning symptoms\n\nAlways consult a healthcare professional for accurate diagnosis and personalized treatment.",
